abstract: The latest version of Itanium, once due in 2007, will ship later this year, marking a string of disappointments for Intel and its decade-old server chip.
snippet: The latest version of Itanium, once due in 2007, will ship later this year, marking a string of disappointments for Intel and its decade-old server chip.
lead_paragraph: Intel has celebrated the 10-year anniversary of the Itanium chip’s first delay with another delay.

headline.main: Ten Years After First Delay, Intel’s Itanium Is Still Late
